{
  "uuid": "b23e1aac0a3d219c9dc4cc636c5be0c8",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The successful individual in this position is responsible for providing technical support for installations, preventive maintenance, relocation, troubleshooting and resolving product performance problems. He/she supports customers primarily in Singapore and Brunei. Occasional overseas travel will be required.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Deliver technical support during installations to ensure successful deployment of products and provide basic operation training to customers</li><li>Execute preventive maintenance activities to sustain optimal product performance and minimize downtime</li><li>Manage equipment relocation processes to maintain operational continuity and ensure customer satisfaction</li><li>Diagnose and resolve product performance issues promptly to reduce impact on customer operations</li><li>Respond effectively to technical inquiries and service requests from customers in Singapore and Brunei</li><li>Accompany sales team on customer visits and site inspections to provide technical support and enhance customer engagement</li><li>Respond to customer queries to support the sales team in addressing technical concerns</li><li>Prepare technical documentation, including official memos and Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), on installation, maintenance, troubleshooting, and repair for customer reference</li><li>Provide technical expertise to the sales team during product seminars and exhibitions to facilitate demonstration of product features</li><li>Coordinate occasional overseas travel to deliver on-site technical assistance and support</li><li>Follow up on warranty claim submissions to ensure timely resolution and customer satisfaction</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Electronics/Electrical Engineering or equivalent</li><li>Minimum of 3 years of relevant field service experience</li><li>Proven troubleshooting and problem-solving skills demonstrated through resolving product performance issues</li><li>Effective oral and written communication skills to interact with customers and internal teams</li></ul><p><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</em></p>",
